1. *Brinula* sam se za svoju sestru kada je bila bolesna. (I was worried about my sister when she was sick.)
2. Ona se *brinula* da će zakasniti na sastanak. (She was worried that she would be late for the meeting.)
3. Kada je videla da je dete povređeno, odmah se *brinula* za njegovo zdravlje. (When she saw that the child was injured, she immediately worried about his health.)
4. Ne trebaš da se *brineš* o novcu, sve ću ja platiti. (You don't need to worry about the money, I will pay for everything.)
5. *Brinući* se za svoju porodicu, radi duplo više nego pre. (By worrying about her family, she works twice as hard as before.)
6. Oni se *ne brinu* mnogo o budućnosti, već žive u sadašnjosti. (They don't worry much about the future, they live in the present.)
7. *Brinuo* sam se da li će sve biti spremno na vreme. (I worried whether everything would be ready on time.)
8. Čim su čuli za poplavu, svi su se *brinuli* za svoje domove. (As soon as they heard about the flood, everyone worried about their homes.)
9. Bez obzira na sve, ona se uvek *brine* o drugima. (Regardless of everything, she always cares about others.)
10. Kada se budeš *brinuo* o svom zdravlju, nećeš morati da ideš kod doktora toliko često. (When you take care of your health, you won't have to go to the doctor so often.)